&lt;General Building Products Corp> isoffering one mln shares of stock at 11 dlrs a share, saidco-managing underwriters, PaineWebber Inc and LadenburgThalmann and Co Inc.    Proceeds from the offering will be used to repay short-termdebt, to finance the opening of new locations and as workingcapital, they said.    The company, headquarted in Medford, N.Y., sells lumber andbuilding supplies to building contractors and, through retailoutlets, to consumers.  Reuter&#3;